channel.title: Intel Pentium 4 > Intel Core 2 Duo e4700
channel.description:
I need some help I'm trying to upgrade form the intel Pentium 4 647 3.20ghz to a Intel Core 2 Duo e4700 2.6 Dual core and I want to make sure my board supports it they are the same socket LGA 775 The Intel core 2 due doesn't look like it has pins and my Intel Pentium 4 Has pins so I really don't know but some help from you guys would be very appreciated, I tried to upgrade to a intel Pentium D Processor once out of a ASUS Pc and it didn't work it wouldn't even boot all the way
My Processor and Socket [img]http://i1166.photobucket.com/albums/q601/Raymond_Iasian_Lawrence/Screenshot_2_zpszxizkleo.png[/img]
My Board [img]http://i1166.photobucket.com/albums/q601/Raymond_Iasian_Lawrence/Screenshot_3_zpsdjbk6p1n.png[/img]
The Processor I'm getting [img]http://i1166.photobucket.com/albums/q601/Raymond_Iasian_Lawrence/Screenshot_4_zpsv1v8lio5.png[/img]
The Processor I have now [img]http://i1166.photobucket.com/albums/q601/Raymond_Iasian_Lawrence/Screenshot_5_zpsbgt4yhyw.png[/img]
*I'm Kinda new to processors do they all have pins? xD or am I just stupid?*
